Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @spring onions{2} then slice thinly. Thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}. Peel and grate the @ginger{1}.

Pop the radish in a #small bowl{} and add the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and the @sugar{1}. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!). Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Remove from the frying pan to a #bowl{} and set aside for later.

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the red onion and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and peppers, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir fry until softened too, ~{5-7%minutes}. Once the veg are soft, add the @king prawns{150%g} to the frying pan and stir fry until starting to go pink, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{300%g} to the frying pan, break them apart gently with your hands first, and stir fry, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the ginger, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @ketjap manis{25%ml} along with a splash of @water{}. Stir through to combine and cook until everything is piping hot and the prawns are cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Divide equally into #bowls{} and top with the pickled radish, spring onion and toasted sesame seeds. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've added prawns to your meal, add them to the pan once the mushrooms and peppers are softened in the step above and cook until starting to go pink, 2-3 mins.

> Step 5 MOD: If you've added prawns to your meal, make sure they are cooked through and piping hot at the end of this step. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.